WEBVTT

00:02.306 --> 00:04.830
[ Door opens, closes ]

00:04.874 --> 00:06.876
[ Dog barking in distance ]

00:06.919 --> 00:10.184
Rox: This is Squad 15,
time 0700, going off-shift.

00:10.227 --> 00:12.838
Jesse: Copy that, Squad 15.
Have a good morning.

00:16.581 --> 00:17.452
[ Door closes ]

00:17.495 --> 00:19.889
-Frying pan?
-Frying pan.

00:19.932 --> 00:21.586
-Salt.
-Salt.

00:21.630 --> 00:24.154
-And --
-Pepper. I'm way ahead of you.

00:27.114 --> 00:31.031
You're using the wrong knife.And you know this how?
Your days as a Ginsu sales rep?

00:31.074 --> 00:33.337
I know this because everybody
knows you use a serrated knife

00:33.381 --> 00:34.686
to cut tomatoes.

00:34.730 --> 00:36.471
Handle first.

00:37.820 --> 00:39.126
-Good morning.
-Morning.

00:39.169 --> 00:40.214
Morning.Hey, I thought you were
playing golf.

00:40.257 --> 00:43.347
-Not today.
-Just got off a shift.

00:43.391 --> 00:45.349
-You hungry?
-I'll take a chance.

00:45.393 --> 00:46.785
How old is that bathrobe?

00:46.829 --> 00:48.178
Older than you.Older than you.

00:48.222 --> 00:51.138
[ Laughs ] Cute.
How do you like your eggs?

00:51.181 --> 00:53.270
Dealer's choice.

00:53.314 --> 00:55.098
[ Telephone rings,
siren wailing in distance ]

00:55.142 --> 00:57.318
Dr. Rorish
was looking for you.

00:57.361 --> 00:59.972
What? I'm only, like,
five minutes late.

01:00.016 --> 01:02.366
[ Telephone continues ringing ]I was looking at apartments.

01:02.410 --> 01:04.020
Ah.

01:04.064 --> 01:05.761
I know. I wasn't ready
to move in with you,

01:05.804 --> 01:07.545
and now I'm getting evicted
by my friend

01:07.589 --> 01:09.895
because her boyfriend's
moving in with her.

01:09.939 --> 01:13.769
Karma. That's what
you're thinking, right?

01:13.812 --> 01:16.467
Really wasn't
thinking anything.

01:16.511 --> 01:18.687
[ Ringing continues,
indistinct conversations ]

01:18.730 --> 01:19.818
[ Sighs ]

01:19.862 --> 01:23.605
[ Dog barking in distance ]

01:28.175 --> 01:31.395
-This is really good.
-You like it, Dad?

01:31.439 --> 01:34.224
I finished it, didn't I?[ Dish clatters ]

01:34.268 --> 01:39.360
I read a terrible thing
on the Facebook last night.

01:39.403 --> 01:40.535
I'm not on "the Facebook."

01:40.578 --> 01:43.842
About Brooks.
You remember him?

01:43.886 --> 01:45.670
-He's dead.
-He's dead?

01:45.714 --> 01:48.456
No details except
about the funeral

01:48.499 --> 01:50.414
in some city called Chino.

01:50.458 --> 01:52.199
-When's the funeral?
-Today.

01:52.242 --> 01:54.157
-Oh, well, we have to go.
-I'm not.

01:54.201 --> 01:57.552
-Dad, he was in Robert's unit.
-We weren't invited.

01:57.595 --> 01:59.815
-Thank you for the breakfast.
-We are both military.

01:59.858 --> 02:02.165
We will go
and show our respects.I don't wanna get into this.

02:02.209 --> 02:04.167
His family came to
Robert's funeral.How would you even get us there?

02:04.211 --> 02:06.126
-We're going.
-We don't have a car.

02:06.169 --> 02:08.128
I do.

02:08.171 --> 02:09.477
I can drive.

02:11.348 --> 02:13.916
So you are
going to this dance?

02:13.959 --> 02:16.310
Are you sure he's up to it?

02:16.353 --> 02:17.702
Last week was
a tough week for him.

02:17.746 --> 02:19.487
Mom, Max has bronchospasms.

02:19.530 --> 02:21.097
He's been dealing with it
for years.

02:21.141 --> 02:23.404
Okay. How'd you get him
to change his mind?

02:23.447 --> 02:25.188
I told him someone else
asked me.

02:25.232 --> 02:28.017
Doesn't matter how old you are,
women got the same tricks.

02:28.060 --> 02:30.802
[ Sirens wailing in distance ]Dr. Kean. Incoming, please.
Let's go.

02:30.846 --> 02:33.153
What do you got?35-year-old male
cycling accident.

02:33.196 --> 02:35.111
Multiple injuries,
vitals stable.

02:35.155 --> 02:37.244
Okay, what do you got here?30-year-old female,
same cycling accident.

02:37.287 --> 02:39.420
Obvious ankle deformities,
stable vitals.

02:39.463 --> 02:42.205
Hi, I'm Dr. Rorish.
This is Dr. Kean over here.[ Woman grunts ]

02:42.249 --> 02:44.251
-Can you tell us what happened?
-I-I got dizzy...

02:44.294 --> 02:45.817
-Okay.
-And I lost control of my bike

02:45.861 --> 02:48.603
and swerved into my husband, Ed,
and we both went down.

02:48.646 --> 02:50.561
-Ed, can you hear me?
-Dr. Rorish, he's altered.

02:50.605 --> 02:52.302
Okay, center stage, please.

02:52.346 --> 02:54.522
"Altered"? What does that mean?Hey, hey, listen,
calm down, okay?

02:54.565 --> 02:56.219
We're gonna take care
of you guys.I'm such an idiot.

02:56.263 --> 02:58.134
"Let's bike uphill
in Griffith Park.

02:58.178 --> 02:59.962
It'll be great exercise."
-Probably was.

03:00.005 --> 03:02.921
-Okay, let's get her to --
-Owen: Stay calm, Max.

03:02.965 --> 03:04.923
WOMAN:
Got another one over here.Owen: It's gonna be okay.

03:04.967 --> 03:07.752
[ Gasping ]

03:07.796 --> 03:09.101
Owen:
Do something, do something!

03:09.145 --> 03:11.626
-[ Gasping ]
-Leanne? Leanne!

03:11.669 --> 03:13.410
-[ Max cries ]
-Owen: Do something.

03:13.454 --> 03:15.847
Leanne!Looks like he has a history
of pulmonary --

03:15.891 --> 03:17.980
Pulmonary adenocarcinoma
in situ.[ Wheezing ]

03:18.023 --> 03:21.113
What happened, Owen?We were watching TV,
and he couldn't breathe.

03:21.157 --> 03:22.985
O2 sat at 82
with a nonrebreather.

03:23.028 --> 03:24.769
-The oxygen. It wasn't working.
-[ Cries ]

03:24.813 --> 03:26.510
I'm right here, son.
I'm right here.It's okay.

03:26.554 --> 03:29.165
He's going in with us, Max,
okay? We've got him.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.471
Get him in, get him in.
All right, incoming.

03:30.514 --> 03:32.516
Rorish:
Everybody ready? On my count.

03:32.560 --> 03:35.824
One, two, three. Watch his head.
Got it?

03:35.867 --> 03:37.086
-We got you, Max.
-Okay.

03:37.129 --> 03:38.435
-We got you.
-Don't -- no, no.

03:38.479 --> 03:40.481
No, no, don't, don't.
You don't need to do that.

03:40.524 --> 03:42.004
I need to examine you
thoroughly.

03:42.047 --> 03:43.310
No one wants to see
what's under there. Trust me.

03:43.353 --> 03:45.790
-They'll all go blind.
-Kathy, we're doctors.

03:45.834 --> 03:47.139
-[ Gasps ]
-Dr. Campbell?

03:47.183 --> 03:48.967
-Is he gonna be okay?
-Campbell: What do we got?

03:49.011 --> 03:51.927
Kathy: He can't breathe.Severely dilated RV
with wall hypokinesis.

03:51.970 --> 03:53.885
-Massive pulmonary embolism.
-Fits the presentation.

03:53.929 --> 03:55.757
Sudden onset
shortness of breath,

03:55.800 --> 03:58.194
tachycardia, hypoxia,
and active cancer.

03:58.238 --> 04:00.414
He's had clots in his legs
before, but never in his lungs.

04:00.457 --> 04:03.460
He needs TPA. How long has he
been on the transplant list?

04:03.504 --> 04:06.028
-Over a year.
-Is he still on anticoagulation?

04:06.071 --> 04:07.508
We just stopped
three months ago.

04:07.551 --> 04:09.249
The blood clot is causing
massive strain to his heart

04:09.292 --> 04:12.382
and to his lungs. We need to
administer a clot buster --

04:12.426 --> 04:14.341
I know what TPA is.
Do whatever it takes.

04:14.384 --> 04:17.300
Okay, all right. Let's go.
Just relax, Max. We got you.Going in.

04:17.344 --> 04:19.084
Campbell: All right, Max.Give it a few more minutes
for the medicine to work, okay?

04:19.128 --> 04:20.564
-Intubation kit just in case.
-There you go.

04:20.608 --> 04:22.349
-Obvious knee deformity.
-What do I got here?

04:22.392 --> 04:25.395
Trace pericardial effusion
and otherwise negative FAST.

04:25.439 --> 04:27.571
Hey, we gotta get him upstairs
for a CT right now.

04:27.615 --> 04:29.094
-What's going on? My leg hurts.
-Ed?

04:29.138 --> 04:31.140
-Aah!
-I'm so sorry. I...

04:31.183 --> 04:32.620
You dislocated your knee, Ed.

04:32.663 --> 04:34.274
We can give you pain meds
and wait for them to kick in,

04:34.317 --> 04:36.058
or I can just snap it back in
place and the pain will go away.

04:36.101 --> 04:37.581
Great. Just do it.

04:37.625 --> 04:38.974
Okay. One, two...[ Bone cracks ]

04:39.017 --> 04:41.455
Aah!Okay. let's get 'em
both upstairs.

04:41.498 --> 04:44.022
-All right, let's go.
-We're waiting on that BiPap.

04:44.066 --> 04:45.676
Hey, Jesse,
you guys need a hand?

04:45.720 --> 04:48.897
No, we got it covered.
O2 sats still 82. No change.

04:48.940 --> 04:50.507
Okay.Okay, BiPap's on your left.
Come on.

04:50.551 --> 04:52.030
We're gonna put a mask on you,
all right, buddy?

04:52.074 --> 04:53.423
-Ready?
-[ Gasps ]

04:53.467 --> 04:55.251
-Max, calm down. I'm right here.
-Dad!

04:55.295 --> 04:58.254
Let's get him to breathe.
Respiratory's at 44.

04:58.298 --> 04:59.951
-What's going on?
-Where is my BiPap?

04:59.995 --> 05:01.083
Ariel: Oh, my God.Guthrie: He's maxed out
all of his oxygen.

05:01.126 --> 05:02.345
Jesse:
BiPap's on your left.

05:02.389 --> 05:04.652
[ Coughs ] Daddy?

05:04.695 --> 05:06.610
Ariel? Ariel,
get outta here now!

05:06.654 --> 05:08.917
-[ Gasps ]
-I want you to leave now!

05:08.960 --> 05:10.832
Jesse:
BP's dropping, guys. Come on.

05:10.875 --> 05:12.703
-Campbell: Give me the BiPap.
-Daddy?

05:12.747 --> 05:15.053
-Come over here. Hold his hand.
-Breathe, Max, breathe.

05:15.097 --> 05:16.794
-[ Max crying ]
-It's okay. It's okay.

05:16.838 --> 05:18.535
-Sats at 70.
-Come on, Max.

05:18.579 --> 05:20.102
-Owen: It's okay.
-[ Gasps ]

05:20.145 --> 05:21.712
-Rorish: I need you to breathe.
-Easy, easy. Take it easy.

05:21.756 --> 05:23.279
-Come on, Max.
-Going to respiratory failure.

05:23.323 --> 05:24.846
[ Machine beeping rapidly ]Just relax, Max. Just relax.

05:24.889 --> 05:27.762
Big breath. Okay. Let's try
one more time. Ready?

05:27.805 --> 05:30.112
-One, two, three.
-Come on, come on, come on.

05:30.155 --> 05:32.070
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ][ Gasps ]

05:32.114 --> 05:33.637
-There we go.
-Thattaboy.

05:33.681 --> 05:35.857
-Oh, boy. Okay. One more time.
-All right, he's holding it.

05:35.900 --> 05:37.554
-Breathe, son. Breathe.
-And...

05:37.598 --> 05:39.077
-That's it.
-Thattaboy.

05:39.121 --> 05:42.254
90% saturation's improving.
Good job, Max. Good job.

05:42.298 --> 05:45.823
-Let's get your son to sides.
-Campbell: Good job, Max.

05:45.867 --> 05:47.608
Is he gonna be okay?

05:47.651 --> 05:51.002
Your son is in critical
condition, but he's stable.

05:51.046 --> 05:54.832
We have to see if the TPA
mitigates the blood clot.

05:54.876 --> 05:57.618
There you go.Good news is,
if he survives this,

05:57.661 --> 05:59.837
he'll be bumped to the top
of the transplant list.

05:59.881 --> 06:07.105
[ Machine beeping steadily ]

06:09.760 --> 06:13.111
[ Telephone rings in distance ]

06:15.375 --> 06:19.074
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over PA ]

06:19.117 --> 06:21.424
Ariel.

06:21.468 --> 06:23.513
I am so sorry
I yelled at you.

06:23.557 --> 06:25.428
Okay? I just didn't want you
to see Max like that.

06:25.472 --> 06:27.125
It's cool.

06:27.169 --> 06:29.301
Oh, honey. Do you want
to talk about it?

06:29.345 --> 06:33.436
No, it's fine. I mean, truth is,
I barely even know him so...

06:33.480 --> 06:36.396
Ariel...

06:36.439 --> 06:39.355
I have to work right now.
Okay?

06:42.184 --> 06:43.881
Okay.

06:43.925 --> 06:53.543
♪♪

07:01.986 --> 07:03.553
[ Button clicks ]Not great news.

07:03.597 --> 07:06.861
X-ray shows your ankle's broken.Broken, broken?

07:06.904 --> 07:10.517
Like I'm gonna need a cast?Yes, like a cast and crutches
and no strenuous activity.

07:10.560 --> 07:13.824
Oh, God. Really?
What am I gonna do now?

07:13.868 --> 07:15.739
You're gonna relax is what
you're gonna do.

07:15.783 --> 07:17.262
Yeah, that's easy for
you to say.

07:17.306 --> 07:19.439
I mean, look at him.
He looks amazing, right?

07:19.482 --> 07:21.266
She's been working out a lot.
She's trying to lose --

07:21.310 --> 07:23.399
Yeah, I already lost 6 pounds.
I'm on a meal plan.

07:23.443 --> 07:26.620
1,800 calories a day.Keep doing that,
but you need to heal.

07:26.663 --> 07:28.622
Then you can start
thinking about exercise.

07:28.665 --> 07:30.493
CT just opened up.
I need to take you upstairs.

07:30.537 --> 07:32.495
Why? What's wrong with him?
Did he break something, too?

07:32.539 --> 07:34.192
Just to be safe.
He had a bad fall.

07:34.236 --> 07:36.064
I'm gonna be fine, Kathy.
Stay positive.

07:36.107 --> 07:38.022
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

07:38.066 --> 07:39.589
I'm just trying to
make him happy.

07:39.633 --> 07:41.939
He's not anymore.
[ Sighs ]

07:41.983 --> 07:46.074
I mean, he married a size 6.
Now look at me.

07:48.293 --> 07:51.079
And what's the standard of care
for suspicion

07:51.122 --> 07:53.342
of significant head trauma
in an emergent setting?

07:53.385 --> 07:56.084
Vital signs, a physical exam,
and a CT scan.

07:56.127 --> 07:57.912
But for Detective Gomez,

07:57.955 --> 08:01.045
no such scan was ordered
until it was too late, right?

08:01.089 --> 08:02.830
The patient declined
treatment.

08:02.873 --> 08:04.440
Detective Gomez wasn't
of sound mind.

08:04.484 --> 08:06.573
Well,
by my estimation, he was.

08:06.616 --> 08:08.357
-By your estimation.
-Yes.

08:08.400 --> 08:10.402
Have you ever made a mistake,
Dr. Dixon,

08:10.446 --> 08:12.143
in a professional setting?

08:12.187 --> 08:14.450
A mistake?

08:14.494 --> 08:17.105
Yeah, of course
I've made a mistake. I'm human.

08:17.148 --> 08:20.369
Haven't you?I'm not being deposed,
Dr. Dixon. You are.

08:22.066 --> 08:24.460
Tell us about all
the mistakes you've made.

08:24.504 --> 08:25.896
Don't spare any details.

08:29.073 --> 08:31.902
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

08:35.819 --> 08:38.474
My granny used to say,

08:38.518 --> 08:42.434
a man only ever tidies up
if he's avoiding something else.

08:42.478 --> 08:43.784
[ Chuckles ]
You were resting.

08:43.827 --> 08:47.004
And you're holding
something back.

08:47.048 --> 08:48.092
Spit it out, Doc.

08:48.136 --> 08:52.575
Tanya, there's been
a development.

08:52.619 --> 08:55.839
Someone else is
getting my lungs.

08:55.883 --> 08:57.580
See, the scoring system
for transplants,

08:57.624 --> 08:59.190
it favors
the sickest patients.

08:59.234 --> 09:03.717
Now you were number one,
and now you're number two.

09:03.760 --> 09:07.634
Doesn't seem...fair.

09:07.677 --> 09:11.202
Yeah. Look, it's getting crowded
in here.

09:11.246 --> 09:12.987
I'm gonna move you downstairs
to the ER

09:13.030 --> 09:15.076
where you can continue
your breathing treatments.

09:15.119 --> 09:16.686
All right?

09:16.730 --> 09:20.211
I liked you a lot better
when you were hiding something.

09:26.653 --> 09:29.220
Up. Five step out. Fold.

09:29.264 --> 09:32.702
[ "Taps" playing ]

09:32.746 --> 09:42.712
♪♪

09:42.756 --> 09:45.497
Ma'am, this flag is presented
on behalf of a grateful nation

09:45.541 --> 09:48.762
for the honorable and faithful
service of your loved one.

09:48.805 --> 09:58.772
♪♪

09:58.815 --> 10:08.782
♪♪

10:08.825 --> 10:10.174
[ Whispers ] Who is that?

10:10.218 --> 10:12.133
[ Door creaks ]

10:12.176 --> 10:14.091
That's Damon,
my brother's best friend.

10:14.135 --> 10:15.789
They did three tours together.

10:19.357 --> 10:22.534
-Found her in v-tach.
-Kathy, can you hear me?

10:22.578 --> 10:25.059
Dizzy.She's unstable. We need to
shock her now.

10:25.102 --> 10:28.192
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

10:28.236 --> 10:29.846
-Charging at 200.
-Clear.

10:29.890 --> 10:33.197
[ Paddles thunk ][ Exhales sharply ] Oh.

10:33.241 --> 10:35.243
Hang a liter of fluids. I need
an EKG and a stat chem 7.What the hell just happened?

10:35.286 --> 10:37.332
You had a dangerous heart rhythm
called v-tach.

10:37.375 --> 10:39.769
Have you had any heart problems
in the past?No. None.

10:39.813 --> 10:41.205
You said you got dizzy
on the bike.

10:41.249 --> 10:42.903
-Did that happen before today?
-No, never.

10:42.946 --> 10:45.601
Oh, my God.
When is my husband coming back?

10:45.645 --> 10:49.300
It won't be too long.[ Exhales deeply ] I really
need him here right now.

10:49.344 --> 10:51.955
Oh. [ Breathing heavily ]

10:51.999 --> 10:53.783
-So how'd the deposition go?
-Awful.

10:53.827 --> 10:55.785
-You wanna talk about it?
-Nope.

10:55.829 --> 10:58.048
[ Curtain rings rattle ]Morning, ladies.

10:58.092 --> 10:59.963
It smells like a bar in here.

11:00.007 --> 11:03.575
Six shots of Mezcal and who
knows how much champagne.Make it stop.

11:03.619 --> 11:05.316
How long has this
been going on?Just today.

11:05.360 --> 11:07.710
I took her to that new place
in Hollywood for brunch.

11:07.754 --> 11:11.061
They had bottomless mimosas,
but that just got her going.It's not even noon.

11:11.105 --> 11:12.454
I'm worried about her.
She keeps complaining about

11:12.497 --> 11:14.761
a sharp pain in her stomach
and her lower back.

11:14.804 --> 11:16.588
Lean back for me.

11:16.632 --> 11:18.939
-Hey, you're cute.
-Does that hurt?

11:18.982 --> 11:22.769
Not when you do it.[ Laughs ] So what's
your move, Hercules?

11:22.812 --> 11:28.688
Nice name.Let's get a CBC, CMP, lipase,
pain meds, and some IV fluids.

11:28.731 --> 11:30.385
-Dr. Guthrie?
-Mm-hmm.

11:30.428 --> 11:33.605
Any day but today.No, I think today might be
the perfect day.

11:33.649 --> 11:37.871
-Stay in the game, kid.
-What are you doing?

11:37.914 --> 11:39.786
-She's not --
-Oh, God. I'm so sorry.

11:39.829 --> 11:41.570
Yes, she is.

11:41.613 --> 11:45.182
I need a mop over here!
Ohh.

11:45.226 --> 11:47.358
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]He's hanging in there.

11:47.402 --> 11:48.620
Good job, Max.

11:48.664 --> 11:54.235
[ Woman speaking indistinctly
over PA ]

11:54.278 --> 11:57.151
I heard there was a boy
getting new lungs.

11:57.194 --> 12:00.197
Yes. Hopefully.

12:00.241 --> 12:02.156
How old is he?

12:02.199 --> 12:04.245
15.

12:07.161 --> 12:10.077
Congratulations.

12:16.126 --> 12:17.911
Ariel knows I'm here,
right?

12:17.954 --> 12:20.652
Hey, where is she, anyway?
Can you help me?

12:20.696 --> 12:23.046
I'll try.

12:23.090 --> 12:28.312
♪♪

12:28.356 --> 12:34.971
[ Helicopter blades whirring,
explosions ]

12:35.015 --> 12:37.017
[ Gunfire ]Got you some food.

12:37.060 --> 12:39.280
Oh, no, thank you.
I'm not hungry.

12:39.323 --> 12:41.325
Damon isn't here.

12:41.369 --> 12:43.066
[ Indistinct conversations ]

12:43.110 --> 12:44.459
[ Whispers ] Thank you.

12:44.502 --> 12:46.200
Excuse me.

12:48.202 --> 12:50.813
[ Sighs ]
You want some food?

12:50.857 --> 12:52.815
Oh, no, thanks.
I'm not hungry.

12:55.339 --> 12:57.559
You two deserve each other.

12:57.602 --> 13:00.257
Lila, I'm so sorry.
Your husband was a hero.

13:00.301 --> 13:01.781
Thank you.

13:01.824 --> 13:04.609
I wish he could see all
the people who came out today.

13:04.653 --> 13:06.437
Then maybe he wouldn't
have done it.

13:06.481 --> 13:08.788
Done what?

13:08.831 --> 13:10.093
You didn't know?

13:14.358 --> 13:16.317
He killed himself, Ethan.

13:17.405 --> 13:20.887
Just like your brother did.

13:20.930 --> 13:22.976
I'm so sorry. Excuse me.

13:23.019 --> 13:25.413
♪♪

13:25.456 --> 13:28.459
[ Gunfire, explosions ]

13:28.503 --> 13:31.201
Hey, are you all right?
What happened in there?

13:31.245 --> 13:33.421
We're here
because of a suicide.

13:33.464 --> 13:35.727
I should've known.

13:35.771 --> 13:38.252
That's three.

13:38.295 --> 13:40.167
Three people in the same unit
have taken their own lives,

13:40.210 --> 13:41.385
and the first one was
my brother.

13:41.429 --> 13:44.432
[ Sighs ]
Ethan, I'm so sorry.

13:44.475 --> 13:47.696
Something happened
over there.

13:47.739 --> 13:50.873
Nobody wants to talk
about it.

13:50.917 --> 13:52.092
I gotta go.

13:52.135 --> 13:54.529
Do you want me
to take you home?
No.

13:54.572 --> 13:56.313
No, I wanna find Damon.

13:56.357 --> 13:58.489
If there's anybody that knows
what really happened over there,

13:58.533 --> 13:59.926
it's him.

14:08.064 --> 14:09.805
This is the place?Think so.

14:09.849 --> 14:13.809
Good 'cause I'm not searching
every motel in town.

14:13.853 --> 14:16.507
-I wanna get out of here.
-I'll be right back.

14:16.551 --> 14:19.641
I really don't know what
he thinks he's doing here.

14:19.684 --> 14:21.686
He's looking for answers.

14:21.730 --> 14:23.950
There aren't any.

14:23.993 --> 14:26.909
What about you?
What are you doing here?

14:26.953 --> 14:29.912
That's a good question.

14:29.956 --> 14:31.696
Figured it was.

14:32.654 --> 14:34.830
[ Knocks on door ]

14:34.874 --> 14:36.527
[ Door unlocks ]

14:36.571 --> 14:38.312
[ Door creaks ]

14:38.355 --> 14:40.227
Ethan, what do you want?

14:40.270 --> 14:42.011
We didn't get to talk
at the funeral.

14:42.055 --> 14:43.056
Don't really feel like talking.

14:43.099 --> 14:46.624
Yeah, neither do I,
but here I am.

14:46.668 --> 14:49.323
What happened over there?[ Door bangs ]

14:49.366 --> 14:53.283
None of your damn business!Robert was my brother.
That makes it my business.

14:58.723 --> 15:02.771
Robert -- he was in charge
of the unit.

15:02.814 --> 15:04.512
What did he tell you?

15:04.555 --> 15:07.994
Nothing. He never spoke
about his time over there.

15:08.037 --> 15:10.953
Maybe he was protecting you.

15:10.997 --> 15:12.824
From what?

15:13.956 --> 15:16.350
From what?

15:18.178 --> 15:21.007
You better pour me one 'cause
I'm not going anywhere.

15:24.924 --> 15:27.187
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

15:27.230 --> 15:29.798
[ Woman speaks indistinctly
over P.A. ]

15:29.841 --> 15:33.584
Max is still asking
for her.

15:33.628 --> 15:35.412
I knew this would happen
eventually.

15:35.456 --> 15:38.154
I just didn't expect it
to be so soon.

15:38.198 --> 15:39.808
I didn't prepare her for --

15:39.851 --> 15:41.941
Nothing you could've done
would've prepared her for this.

15:41.984 --> 15:45.683
Maybe I shouldn't have
let her...Find a friend?

15:45.727 --> 15:49.252
She doesn't want to see him
because it'll hurt too much.

15:49.296 --> 15:53.213
Yeah...You have to teach her
it will hurt more not to.

15:53.256 --> 15:56.999
[ Siren wailing in distance ]

15:57.043 --> 16:00.002
Pancreatitis.

16:00.046 --> 16:02.874
So, like, a little azithro,
and I'll be good, right?

16:02.918 --> 16:04.093
No, I'm afraid it's more
serious than that.

16:04.137 --> 16:06.748
I'm online. It says fluids
and painkillers.

16:06.791 --> 16:08.315
Oh, does this mean I get oxy?

16:08.358 --> 16:10.012
Listen, people die
from pancreatitis.

16:10.056 --> 16:12.145
Now hopefully,
fluids will do the trick,

16:12.188 --> 16:16.932
but it's a waiting game.But I still might be able to
get out of here tonight, right?

16:16.976 --> 16:20.544
Listen...She's always been a hot mess,
but in a totally free spirit

16:20.588 --> 16:23.983
I wish I could be that
unself-aware kind of way.

16:24.026 --> 16:26.811
Oh, I wish I could be, too.Everything comes so easily
for her --

16:26.855 --> 16:29.118
parties, vacations, guys.

16:29.162 --> 16:32.121
When she's around, they hardly
notice anyone else.

16:32.165 --> 16:34.297
I don't believe that.
You're noticeable.

16:34.341 --> 16:37.213
Oh, great. You actually found
a word worse than "cute."

16:37.257 --> 16:40.564
No, no, all right. That was --
That was poor word choice.

16:40.608 --> 16:43.219
Anyway, I'm sure it'll make her
a great lawyer someday.

16:43.263 --> 16:46.005
-She's in law school?
-Yeah. Why?

16:46.048 --> 16:47.702
Makes sense. That's all.

16:47.745 --> 16:51.967
Hey, Dr. Delicious,
get over here. Selfie time.

16:52.011 --> 16:54.143
No, thanks. I'm good.

16:54.187 --> 16:57.016
[ Telephone ringing
in distance ]

16:59.061 --> 17:00.976
What's v-tach?Your wife had a minor
cardiac event.

17:01.020 --> 17:02.456
We're trying to figure out
what caused it.

17:02.499 --> 17:04.371
She works out every day
for, like, hours.

17:04.414 --> 17:06.721
Every day? That is insane.

17:06.764 --> 17:07.939
He's never been
to the gym, so...

17:07.983 --> 17:09.767
Great. Now I'm overweight
and sensitive.

17:09.811 --> 17:11.987
No, you're fine. Okay?
Everybody's fine.

17:12.031 --> 17:14.033
I'm so sick of talking
about weight.

17:14.076 --> 17:16.035
Okay, I'll go upstairs
and check on your CT.

17:16.078 --> 17:19.081
You know what we did
after we got married?

17:19.125 --> 17:22.041
I mean, like, right after
we said, "I do."

17:22.084 --> 17:24.260
We got naked
and ran into the ocean.

17:24.304 --> 17:25.957
And she looked amazing.

17:26.001 --> 17:27.307
Half the wedding party
joined us.

17:27.350 --> 17:29.222
That's who she used to be.

17:29.265 --> 17:32.486
That's who... [ Slurs ]

17:32.529 --> 17:34.183
-Hey, you feeling okay?
-Pressure's dropping. 60/40.

17:34.227 --> 17:36.055
Need a portable ultrasound!

17:36.098 --> 17:39.710
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

17:39.754 --> 17:42.800
[ Whooshing ]Damn it.
Pericardial tamponade.

17:42.844 --> 17:45.629
The blood is building up around
the heart. It can't contract.

17:45.673 --> 17:48.545
What's happening? Edwin?Hey, it's okay.
We're taking care of him.

17:48.589 --> 17:50.286
We're gonna do
a pericardiocentesis right now.

17:50.330 --> 17:53.115
Risa, page Campbell
and Rorish now.No, we don't have time.

17:53.159 --> 17:55.161
I need a needle and a syringe.
His heart is barely beating.

17:55.204 --> 17:57.293
If we don't do this now, he will
never make it up to the OR.Need a liter of bolus.

17:57.337 --> 18:00.209
Please, tell me
what's happening.We're gonna drain the fluid
that's squeezing

18:00.253 --> 18:01.645
your husband's heart.

18:01.689 --> 18:04.126
You don't wanna watch this,
okay? I mean it.

18:04.170 --> 18:05.301
-All right. You ready?
-Let's do this.

18:05.345 --> 18:07.651
Okay.

18:07.695 --> 18:09.566
[ Door opens ]

18:09.610 --> 18:12.830
Hey. They found
suitable lungs for Max.

18:12.874 --> 18:14.876
-I thought you should know.
-Where?

18:14.919 --> 18:16.182
Bakersfield.

18:16.225 --> 18:18.836
Okay, so what's --
what's the problem?

18:18.880 --> 18:20.969
Well, there could be delays.

18:21.012 --> 18:24.190
It takes time to harvest
the lungs and bring them here.

18:24.233 --> 18:28.150
If Max's condition worsens,

18:28.194 --> 18:30.457
he might not be viable
for the transplant.

18:30.500 --> 18:35.810
Yeah. That makes sense.

18:35.853 --> 18:37.290
Ariel.

18:40.467 --> 18:42.556
He wants to see you.

18:42.599 --> 18:45.254
Did you know that -- that
Woodrow Wilson was

18:45.298 --> 18:47.996
the only President buried
in Washington, D.C.?

18:48.039 --> 18:49.432
Look at me.

18:49.476 --> 18:51.173
He also had basically no
political experience

18:51.217 --> 18:54.176
when he was elected.You need to stop doing this
and go see him.

18:54.220 --> 18:56.483
-I have homework.
-Okay, stop acting like this.

18:56.526 --> 18:58.224
Like what? Like how I feel?
He's going to die.This isn't about you.

18:58.267 --> 19:00.835
This is about who does Max
want to be with him

19:00.878 --> 19:03.577
in the worst moment
of his life? And it's you.

19:03.620 --> 19:06.754
No! No. He might die.
You're right.

19:06.797 --> 19:10.105
I'm sorry, but this is
real life, and in real life,

19:10.149 --> 19:12.803
we are responsible for
the people we care about.

19:12.847 --> 19:16.198
You can't just ignore him.

19:16.242 --> 19:22.683
♪♪

19:22.726 --> 19:24.685
Blood's clotting too fast.
The needle's clogged.

19:24.728 --> 19:26.382
We need a bigger needle.
Find a 16-gauge or larger.

19:26.426 --> 19:28.602
No, that's not gonna work.
Give me a scalpel.

19:28.645 --> 19:31.039
You're gonna cut down
to his heart right here?

19:31.082 --> 19:32.388
We don't have a choice.

19:32.432 --> 19:33.563
The blood is filling up faster
than this needle

19:33.607 --> 19:36.392
can pull it out.
Hang 4 units of PRBCs.

19:36.436 --> 19:39.830
Angus. You sure you got this?I need to make
a hole big enough

19:39.874 --> 19:42.268
so that all the blood
can get out.You do that, he'll keep
losing blood.

19:42.311 --> 19:44.139
You may save his heart, but he
could die of hemorrhaging.

19:44.183 --> 19:45.749
-That's why I hung the blood.
-And what if it can't keep up?

19:45.793 --> 19:47.186
I just need to buy him enough
time to get him to the OR.

19:47.229 --> 19:50.319
Look,
are you with me or not?

19:50.363 --> 19:53.235
-Yes.
-Retractor to Dr. Savetti.

19:53.279 --> 19:56.195
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

19:58.284 --> 20:00.024
All right, there's
the pericardium.

20:00.068 --> 20:02.592
-Clamps and scissors.
-Ready to suction.

20:04.377 --> 20:05.508
Okay, ready?

20:05.552 --> 20:07.380
Okay, cutting now.

20:07.423 --> 20:09.425
[ Suction whooshes ]

20:09.469 --> 20:11.253
[ Monitor beeping erratically ]

20:11.297 --> 20:12.994
Risa:
Pressure's coming back up.

20:13.037 --> 20:15.039
We need to get him
on the bypass.
Let's get him upstairs now.

20:15.083 --> 20:16.998
[ Crying] Is he gonna be okay?
Did it work?

20:17.041 --> 20:21.220
Yes.
He's going up to surgery.

20:21.263 --> 20:23.222
This doctor just saved
your husband's life.

20:23.265 --> 20:25.920
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

20:30.403 --> 20:33.362
Recognize the guy
in the middle?

20:33.406 --> 20:37.366
That's Robert.

20:37.410 --> 20:40.369
Everyone in the picture is dead
except me now.

20:40.413 --> 20:43.416
I'm next.

20:43.459 --> 20:45.418
[ Liquor sloshing ]

20:45.461 --> 20:48.116
You're gonna drink yourself
to death? Is that the plan?

20:48.159 --> 20:50.205
[ Liquor sloshing ]

20:50.249 --> 20:51.989
[ Glass shatters ]

20:53.817 --> 20:57.517
Everybody in the picture
seems happy.

20:57.560 --> 20:59.693
What happened?

20:59.736 --> 21:01.738
You need to leave.

21:01.782 --> 21:04.306
What happened?

21:04.350 --> 21:06.395
[ Sniffles ]

21:09.920 --> 21:11.574
I said leave me alone.

21:14.621 --> 21:15.839
Whatever happened
over there,

21:15.883 --> 21:18.581
it doesn't need to kill
anyone else.

21:20.453 --> 21:22.977
Put the gun down.

21:28.678 --> 21:30.376
He was a high-value target.

21:30.419 --> 21:33.335
Been trading convoys
for months.

21:33.379 --> 21:37.252
Intel placed him in a little
house outside of Marjeh.

21:37.296 --> 21:42.301
But intel had been
letting us down for weeks.

21:42.344 --> 21:44.128
Robert didn't care.

21:44.172 --> 21:47.349
He wanted to bag the guy.

21:48.350 --> 21:50.570
Guard comes out to take
a leak.

21:50.613 --> 21:52.746
He saw us.

21:52.789 --> 21:54.138
Robert gave the order.

21:54.182 --> 21:56.053
[ Gunfire,
indistinct shouting ]

21:56.097 --> 21:59.230
And we lit it up so bad,
the roof came down.

21:59.274 --> 22:02.016
When we went inside,
they were all dead.

22:02.059 --> 22:02.973
Who?

22:03.017 --> 22:05.846
[ Children shouting ]

22:05.889 --> 22:08.370
Kids.

22:08.414 --> 22:12.461
Every single one of them
was covered in blood.

22:12.505 --> 22:15.551
I counted 23.
Clutching toys.

22:15.595 --> 22:18.859
[ Sniffles ]

22:18.902 --> 22:21.340
All dead. [ Sniffles ]

22:21.383 --> 22:24.952
I'm sorry.

22:24.995 --> 22:27.476
[ Exhales deeply ]

22:29.217 --> 22:32.481
Your brother
had it the worst.

22:32.525 --> 22:34.440
He was in charge.

22:34.483 --> 22:37.051
He made the call.

22:37.094 --> 22:40.750
He knew it was his fault.

22:40.794 --> 22:43.362
Robert killed us all
that day,

22:43.405 --> 22:46.321
and now you have to
live with it.

22:46.365 --> 22:48.497
-I don't anymore.
-No!

22:48.541 --> 22:49.542
[ Gunshot ]

22:55.417 --> 22:57.332
Rox: [ Muffled voice ]
Willis! Open the door![ Pounding on door ]

22:57.376 --> 23:00.335
Willis, open it!Damon: [ Distorted voice ]
He knew it was his fault.

23:00.379 --> 23:03.904
-Willis, what happened?
-Get out.

23:03.947 --> 23:05.079
Willis!

23:05.122 --> 23:07.995
Damon: It was his fault.

23:08.038 --> 23:11.346
Willis!The bullet missed his brain,
but it fractured his skull.

23:11.390 --> 23:14.175
Okay, he's breathing on his own.
He must've been knocked
unconscious from the blast.

23:14.218 --> 23:15.437
Give me that shirt.

23:15.481 --> 23:17.570
I'll hold the pressure.

23:17.613 --> 23:20.921
Dad, start the car.
Dad!

23:22.488 --> 23:24.707
[ Door closes ]

23:26.405 --> 23:29.495
You did a pericardial window
in sides?
Yep.

23:29.538 --> 23:32.367
You're supposed
to be a surgeon now,
not an ER cowboy.

23:32.411 --> 23:34.717
You put me in a position
to make the call, and I made it.

23:34.761 --> 23:37.981
He was about to code.
If we hadn't made an opening
for continuous drainage,

23:38.025 --> 23:40.636
he never would've made it
to your table.Okay, slow your roll.

23:42.203 --> 23:43.378
And it's our table.

23:43.422 --> 23:46.686
[ Scrubbing hands ]

23:46.729 --> 23:48.818
[ Door opens ]

23:50.472 --> 23:52.518
[ Tires screech ]

23:52.561 --> 23:53.910
[ Engine revving ]

23:53.954 --> 23:56.522
-I need some help here!
-What the hell happened?!

23:56.565 --> 23:57.914
I'm a doctor from Los Angeles.

23:57.958 --> 24:00.439
Got a self-inflicted
gunshot wound to the head.

24:00.482 --> 24:02.615
He's out from the blast force,
GCS 9.3...2...1.

24:02.658 --> 24:05.269
He's gonna need an IV
and a CT scan. Page neurology.

24:05.313 --> 24:07.315
Do what he says now!

24:07.358 --> 24:11.493
[ Indistinct shouting ]

24:11.537 --> 24:14.017
O2 sats at 75.

24:14.061 --> 24:15.366
Are you gonna have to
intubate him?

24:15.410 --> 24:17.020
We're gonna put it off
as long as we can.

24:17.064 --> 24:19.588
He might never make it off
the vent.

24:19.632 --> 24:21.721
[ Exhales deeply ]

24:21.764 --> 24:23.331
Where's Ariel?

24:23.374 --> 24:25.420
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

24:25.464 --> 24:27.161
I'm sorry, Max.

24:27.204 --> 24:29.468
She's having a hard time
with this.

24:29.511 --> 24:33.907
It's okay.

24:33.950 --> 24:36.387
I understand.

24:36.431 --> 24:40.740
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

24:40.783 --> 24:42.524
She'shaving a hard time?
What is thatsupposed to mean?

24:42.568 --> 24:45.222
Okay, Owen,
I know you're upset.Yeah, upset?

24:45.266 --> 24:46.920
I never wanted Ariel with Max
in the first place.

24:46.963 --> 24:48.704
I told you that he needed
to focus on his health.

24:48.748 --> 24:51.490
Owen, I don't --But now he needs her.
And she can't be bothered?

24:51.533 --> 24:53.274
What is she doing?
Folding linens?

24:53.317 --> 24:55.929
-She's a scared kid.
-Right, and you're her mother.

24:55.972 --> 24:58.148
Do something. You know
what she means to him.

24:58.192 --> 25:00.411
I've already spoken to her.

25:00.455 --> 25:02.675
I can't force her to walk
into the room.

25:06.896 --> 25:10.073
When can I see my husband?
Soon, when he's out of surgery.

25:10.117 --> 25:12.598
He needs a little time,
but he's gonna be just fine.

25:12.641 --> 25:15.992
-Oh, God. I'm so grateful.
-We need to talk about you.

25:16.036 --> 25:17.690
We did a CK test
and we found out

25:17.733 --> 25:19.605
that you have
severe muscle breakdown.
It's called Rhabdomyolysis.

25:19.648 --> 25:22.564
Are...are you saying that
all this happened because

25:22.608 --> 25:27.917
I exercise too much?Yes, you just have to give
the workouts a break.

25:27.961 --> 25:30.311
-That's all.
-That's all?

25:30.354 --> 25:32.792
[ Chuckles ]

25:32.835 --> 25:35.577
What size are you? Zero?

25:35.621 --> 25:36.839
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

25:36.883 --> 25:39.842
I was a dancer.

25:39.886 --> 25:42.279
Thin was mandatory.

25:42.323 --> 25:45.108
I lived on oatmeal and maybe
a couple gummy bears

25:45.152 --> 25:47.633
for sugar rush.

25:47.676 --> 25:50.244
I was exhausted
all the time.

25:50.287 --> 25:52.768
Hating myself for even
the slightest gain.

25:52.812 --> 25:55.162
I ravaged my body to be
something someone else

25:55.205 --> 25:56.511
wanted me to be.

25:56.555 --> 25:59.601
I still deal with what I did
to myself every day.

25:59.645 --> 26:03.649
I'm sorry. You know,
I made assumptions,

26:03.692 --> 26:06.521
which is what I hate
about everyone else.

26:08.567 --> 26:10.743
You need to talk
to your husband.

26:10.786 --> 26:13.615
If he doesn't love you
for who you are,

26:13.659 --> 26:15.182
he shouldn't be
your husband.

26:19.142 --> 26:22.145
How long is this gonna take?
There's a party in
the Hills tonight.

26:22.189 --> 26:25.801
Amber, you can't go out tonight.
Look around you.
You're in a hospital.

26:25.845 --> 26:28.151
Oh, you are such a buzzkill.
Why do I even hang out with you?

26:28.195 --> 26:31.590
All right, enough! You're lucky
that the pancreatitis
didn't kill you.

26:31.633 --> 26:33.592
And if Lana hadn't brought you
to the hospital, you'd be dead.

26:33.635 --> 26:36.290
I think you made your point,
Dr. Dixon.

26:36.333 --> 26:39.075
Excuse me. Look, I know
you're having a bad day --

26:39.119 --> 26:42.122
You know what? I'm just
so sick of lawyers.

26:42.165 --> 26:45.038
Excuse me, but she didn't do
your deposition.

26:45.081 --> 26:48.781
So right now the only thing
that young lady is to you
is a patient.

26:48.824 --> 26:52.872
♪♪

26:52.915 --> 26:56.745
[ Siren wailing in distance,
telephone ringing ]

26:56.789 --> 27:01.402
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:01.445 --> 27:06.668
♪♪

27:06.712 --> 27:09.279
[ Sighs ]

27:09.323 --> 27:13.327
[ Monitor beeping steadily ]

27:13.370 --> 27:19.420
♪♪

27:19.463 --> 27:23.076
Oh. You really have cancer?
I thought you were joking.

27:23.119 --> 27:25.905
[ Chuckles ]

27:25.948 --> 27:28.298
-I'll be back in a bit.
-Good idea.

27:28.342 --> 27:31.650
Hi, kid.

27:31.693 --> 27:33.695
Hi.

27:33.739 --> 27:38.178
I'm sorry
I wasn't here before.

27:38.221 --> 27:42.748
[ Gasps loudly ]

27:42.791 --> 27:44.619
I'm just glad
you're here now.

27:44.663 --> 27:48.144
[ Indistinct conversations ]

27:48.188 --> 27:50.016
How are the lungs?

27:50.059 --> 27:52.105
[ Exhales deeply ]
Supposed to be on their way,

27:52.148 --> 27:56.544
but... [ Exhales deeply ]
they've been saying that
for a while now.

27:56.587 --> 28:00.679
-[ Exhales deeply ]
-It's okay. It's okay.

28:00.722 --> 28:04.900
-[ Exhales deeply ]
-It can take a while.

28:04.944 --> 28:08.730
My dad -- he gave his heart
to this little girl

28:08.774 --> 28:11.602
when he died,
and she waited forever.

28:11.646 --> 28:14.649
Yeah.

28:14.693 --> 28:20.611
He died,
but...not completely.

28:20.655 --> 28:23.049
He still lives on in her.

28:23.092 --> 28:25.747
-[ Exhales deeply ]
-No.

28:25.791 --> 28:28.707
-Just...
-[ Exhales deeply ]

28:28.750 --> 28:30.709
One more thing.

28:30.752 --> 28:34.495
I...I love you.

28:34.538 --> 28:37.454
[ Breathing heavily ]

28:37.498 --> 28:40.719
[ Exhales deeply ]

28:47.595 --> 28:51.077
[ Whispers ]
I love you, too.

28:51.120 --> 29:00.739
♪♪

29:00.782 --> 29:03.654
Let's go, people.
The lungs are on the chopper.

29:03.698 --> 29:07.484
-Jesse: How far out?
-15 minutes give or take.

29:07.528 --> 29:10.096
Campbell: Okay, we're taking him
upstairs for prep.

29:10.139 --> 29:11.924
Jesse: Let's move him out, guys.
Let's go.

29:11.967 --> 29:14.622
[ Indistinct conversations ]

29:14.665 --> 29:16.798
Jesse: Ready to grab
those doors? Let's go.

29:16.842 --> 29:19.018
[ Telephone ringing,
siren wailing in distance ]

29:19.061 --> 29:22.238
I hope he told you
what you wanted to hear.

29:22.282 --> 29:26.590
The only secret is war itself.
Terrible things happen there.

29:26.634 --> 29:29.768
But when you get home,
you move on.

29:29.811 --> 29:32.596
You reopened old wounds.

29:32.640 --> 29:36.992
That man wouldn't be here
if you hadn't...

29:37.036 --> 29:40.213
Hadn't what?

29:40.256 --> 29:42.345
I'm gonna go sit with him.

29:42.389 --> 29:45.653
[ Footsteps depart ]

29:45.696 --> 29:47.829
I don't know how
to save him.

29:47.873 --> 29:49.309
[ Sighs ]

29:49.352 --> 29:51.920
He thinks you're the guy
that needs saving.

29:51.964 --> 29:53.443
You know that, right?

29:55.750 --> 29:57.708
Ethan's the one
who found him --

29:57.752 --> 30:00.668
Robert hanging
in his living room.

30:00.711 --> 30:03.018
Had to cut him down.

30:03.062 --> 30:06.152
Oh, my God.

30:06.195 --> 30:08.154
That's why I'm selling
that house.

30:08.197 --> 30:10.460
My son is living
in his brother's coffin,

30:10.504 --> 30:12.680
and he can't get out.

30:12.723 --> 30:20.819
♪♪

30:20.862 --> 30:23.865
Where am I?

30:23.909 --> 30:25.824
The hospital.

30:28.261 --> 30:32.221
I'm sorry. I shouldn't have
pushed you like that.

30:32.265 --> 30:35.355
I was gonna do it anyway.

30:35.398 --> 30:36.791
Brought the gun...

30:39.185 --> 30:42.710
If anything,
you saved my life...

30:42.753 --> 30:44.190
for now.

30:44.233 --> 30:49.804
I'm sorry,
but I don't give up.

30:49.848 --> 30:51.414
I'm gonna get you help.

30:53.939 --> 30:56.855
Your brother was broken
before he went to war.

30:56.898 --> 31:01.685
And so was I.
That's why we were friends.

31:03.600 --> 31:06.995
You can't help me like
you couldn't help him.

31:11.695 --> 31:14.655
Get an ETA on that chopper.

31:14.698 --> 31:17.440
[ Exhales deeply ]
How long will this take?

31:17.484 --> 31:20.313
Next thing you know,
you'll be breathing
with a new set of lungs.

31:20.356 --> 31:23.098
Max. Max, are you with me?

31:23.142 --> 31:24.795
I'm dizzy.

31:24.839 --> 31:25.971
[ Gasping ]

31:26.014 --> 31:27.581
Push those meds.
We need to intubate now.

31:27.624 --> 31:28.799
[ Coughing ][ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

31:28.843 --> 31:30.845
-He's in v-fib.
-Will, intubate now.

31:30.889 --> 31:33.848
One of epi. Crash cart.
Get me those paddles.
You take over. Ready?

31:33.892 --> 31:36.024
[ Monitor beeping rapidly ]

31:36.068 --> 31:39.375
[ Paddles charging ]Campbell: Clear.

31:39.419 --> 31:40.724
[ Paddles thunk ]Where the hell are those lungs?

31:40.768 --> 31:42.552
Angus: They're on the roof now.Again. Clear.

31:42.596 --> 31:44.903
[ Paddles thunk ]Again. Clear.

31:44.946 --> 31:45.904
[ Paddles thunk ]

31:51.126 --> 31:52.519
[ Elevator bell dings ]

31:52.562 --> 32:02.529
♪♪

32:02.572 --> 32:08.361
♪♪

32:08.404 --> 32:10.798
Left lung first.

32:10.841 --> 32:20.808
♪♪

32:20.851 --> 32:22.157
Are they all done?

32:22.201 --> 32:30.731
♪♪

32:30.774 --> 32:32.298
How does it fit?

32:32.341 --> 32:34.213
It fits good.

32:34.256 --> 32:39.783
♪♪

32:39.827 --> 32:42.003
We're lucky she was a match.

32:43.526 --> 32:47.661
Ariel, Max's breathing
got worse.

32:47.704 --> 32:52.535
He wasn't able to have
the operation.

32:52.579 --> 32:54.059
Okay,
so can they save the lungs,

32:54.102 --> 32:57.366
or does he have to wait
for new ones?

32:57.410 --> 32:59.151
There is no easy way
to say this.

32:59.194 --> 33:00.935
-I wanna go see him.
-Ariel.

33:00.979 --> 33:03.111
He must feel horrible.

33:03.155 --> 33:06.027
I'm terribly sorry.

33:06.071 --> 33:11.163
I promise you,
we did everything we could.

33:13.078 --> 33:16.081
-No. You didn't.
-Ariel, do you wanna go home?

33:16.124 --> 33:19.606
We will leave right now.No I don't wanna go home.
I want you to go do your job.

33:19.649 --> 33:22.130
If he had gotten his lungs
earlier,

33:22.174 --> 33:23.784
he'd be alive right now.

33:23.827 --> 33:27.353
No, he'd be more than alive.
He'd be all better.

33:27.396 --> 33:30.095
You waited too long.

33:30.138 --> 33:32.706
[ Voice breaking ] It's your
fault he's dead right now.

33:36.101 --> 33:40.061
[ Sniffles ]

33:44.283 --> 33:47.025
How long am I gonna be
like this?

33:47.068 --> 33:49.331
We'll have you on
a Fentanyl drip for 24 hours.

33:49.375 --> 33:51.594
Tomorrow, we can try
getting you up,
maybe going for a walk.

33:51.638 --> 33:54.641
Hey, relax. You're young.

33:54.684 --> 33:57.078
People in your situation
can do a full marathon
in less than a year.

33:57.122 --> 34:00.777
Ed. Oh, God. You look...

34:00.821 --> 34:03.258
[ Crying ] I am so sorry.

34:03.302 --> 34:06.218
It's not your fault.
Don't blame yourself for this.

34:06.261 --> 34:09.134
Hey, he's gonna get better.

34:09.177 --> 34:11.136
You both are.

34:11.179 --> 34:13.834
We need to get better.
We really do.

34:13.877 --> 34:15.488
What's that supposed
to mean?

34:15.531 --> 34:21.233
I almost killed myself.
I almost killed you.

34:21.276 --> 34:24.540
God, I can't keep trying to be
the person I was five years ago.

34:24.584 --> 34:26.194
I don't care
how much you weigh.

34:26.238 --> 34:29.110
Then why do you make me
go for a bike ride
every morning at 5?

34:29.154 --> 34:32.592
Because I don't want you
to hate yourself anymore.

34:32.635 --> 34:35.464
You don't wanna go
to the beach

34:35.508 --> 34:37.205
because you're
too embarrassed.

34:37.249 --> 34:39.425
You don't even wanna leave
the house.

34:39.468 --> 34:42.602
You won't let me
touch you.

34:42.645 --> 34:45.474
I'd like to go to the beach.

34:45.518 --> 34:47.172
I wanna touch you.

34:47.215 --> 34:50.436
[ Whispers ] You do?

34:52.177 --> 34:56.442
I don't have a problem
with this. You do.

34:56.485 --> 35:06.191
♪♪

35:06.234 --> 35:10.238
Is that it?
Anything else to sign?

35:10.282 --> 35:12.545
No, you're good to go.

35:12.588 --> 35:14.373
I forgot my phone.
Can you go get it?

35:14.416 --> 35:16.157
I can't go back there.
It's too disgusting.

35:16.201 --> 35:19.595
-No, you go get your phone.
-I'll get it.

35:19.639 --> 35:21.423
I'll go with you.

35:21.467 --> 35:24.252
I am so sick of her.

35:24.296 --> 35:26.515
Yeah, me, too.
And I just met her.[ Chuckles ]

35:26.559 --> 35:28.169
Why don't you throw
her phone away

35:28.213 --> 35:29.779
and tell her
you couldn't find it?

35:29.823 --> 35:32.217
Then she'd have a heart attack
and actually die this time.

35:32.260 --> 35:33.870
[ Laughs ] Well, she'd sue me.
That's why.

35:33.914 --> 35:36.351
Plus I already have
a lawsuit so...

35:36.395 --> 35:37.874
Oh, well, we'd countersue.

35:37.918 --> 35:40.138
I'm gonna be a better lawyer
than her, anyways.

35:40.181 --> 35:41.400
Wait, you're in law school,
too?

35:41.443 --> 35:42.662
Yeah.

35:42.705 --> 35:44.968
I honestly didn't know
there were nice lawyers.

35:45.012 --> 35:46.535
Well, it sounds like
you need one.

35:46.579 --> 35:50.148
Do you wanna have a drink
sometime?

35:50.191 --> 35:52.498
Yes. [ Laughs ]

35:52.541 --> 35:56.719
So is Hercules talking to her
or flirting with her?

35:56.763 --> 35:59.983
-Looks like both.
-She's not the patient, right?

36:00.027 --> 36:02.986
Nope. He can do anything
he wants now.

36:03.030 --> 36:05.859
How did his deposition go?

36:05.902 --> 36:08.427
Not as good
as this is going.

36:08.470 --> 36:10.211
[ Chuckling ]

36:10.255 --> 36:13.214
Family of the Year:
♪ Let me go

36:13.258 --> 36:19.394
♪ I don't wanna be your hero

36:19.438 --> 36:23.920
♪ I don't wanna be
your big man ♪

36:23.964 --> 36:28.708
♪ Just wanna fight
with everyone else ♪

36:28.751 --> 36:33.016
♪ Your masquerade

36:33.060 --> 36:35.236
Hey, I should be honest
about something.

36:35.280 --> 36:36.890
Clearly, it helps.

36:36.933 --> 36:39.806
I really wanted you
to move in with me.

36:39.849 --> 36:43.070
I was kind of bummed
you didn't.

36:43.113 --> 36:45.246
-I'm sorry.
-It's okay.

36:45.290 --> 36:47.770
We can do this at your pace.
I'm fine with that.Okay.

36:47.814 --> 36:49.250
You should check
the bulletin board.

36:49.294 --> 36:50.643
Risa's looking
for a roommate.

36:50.686 --> 36:52.297
I'm not sure how you feel
about Risa.

36:52.340 --> 36:53.776
I can't have kids.

36:53.820 --> 36:55.256
Excuse me?

36:55.300 --> 36:58.433
I treated my body so badly,
I have, uh,

36:58.477 --> 37:00.870
ovarian insufficiency.

37:00.914 --> 37:03.264
But it may still be possible
you could have --

37:03.308 --> 37:05.092
I just didn't wanna
mislead you

37:05.135 --> 37:08.400
if I moved in
and you found out.

37:08.443 --> 37:09.618
You're looking at me weird.

37:09.662 --> 37:11.664
No, I'm fine. I never
wanted kids anyway.

37:11.707 --> 37:15.276
-You don't? I do.
-You just said --

37:15.320 --> 37:16.321
There's a lot of different ways
you can have kids.

37:16.364 --> 37:18.236
-You can adopt, I mean...
-I know.

37:18.279 --> 37:19.367
You really don't wanna
have kids?

37:19.411 --> 37:20.934
-I didn't --
-I'm shocked.

37:20.977 --> 37:22.327
Why are we having
this conversation?

37:22.370 --> 37:24.111
We're not even
living together.

37:24.154 --> 37:28.158
I just...wanted you to know

37:28.202 --> 37:30.117
in case it mattered.

37:30.160 --> 37:33.294
♪♪

37:33.338 --> 37:35.427
It doesn't.

37:35.470 --> 37:37.037
Okay.

37:37.080 --> 37:39.518
♪ But I'm a kid
like everyone else ♪

37:39.561 --> 37:41.084
Okay.

37:43.348 --> 37:46.786
I like Risa, but I don't
wanna live with her.

37:46.829 --> 37:49.267
I wanna live with you.

37:49.310 --> 37:51.443
♪ Ooh, ooh

37:51.486 --> 37:57.362
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

37:57.405 --> 38:02.105
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

38:02.149 --> 38:06.066
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh,
ooh, ooh ♪

38:06.109 --> 38:09.591
Hey. I don't wanna intrude.

38:09.635 --> 38:11.680
If there's anything
I can do...

38:15.684 --> 38:17.860
No.

38:17.904 --> 38:19.297
Thank you.

38:19.340 --> 38:24.127
Everyone has been so kind.

38:24.171 --> 38:26.129
We knew this day would come.

38:29.872 --> 38:32.266
He's going to be buried
with his mother.

38:34.703 --> 38:36.096
I-I didn't realize.

38:36.139 --> 38:40.970
He never knew her.
He was only 3 when she died.

38:41.014 --> 38:43.930
Youknew her.

38:43.973 --> 38:46.280
[ Voice breaking ] I did.

38:54.419 --> 38:56.290
I know what
you're going through.

38:56.334 --> 38:59.380
Uh, no. You don't.

38:59.424 --> 39:02.165
You're afraid if
you start crying,

39:02.209 --> 39:05.778
you might
never be able to stop.

39:05.821 --> 39:10.348
It's hard to imagine,
but...you will.

39:13.133 --> 39:14.482
I lost my family, too.

39:16.354 --> 39:17.877
I know.

39:17.920 --> 39:22.751
The pain is almost
too much to bear.

39:22.795 --> 39:28.409
♪♪

39:28.453 --> 39:31.760
He was...he was
a beautiful boy -- Owen.

39:31.804 --> 39:34.546
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

39:34.589 --> 39:36.025
[ Sobbing ]

39:36.069 --> 39:41.683
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

39:41.727 --> 39:47.385
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

39:47.428 --> 39:54.043
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

39:54.087 --> 39:58.439
♪ So let me go

39:58.483 --> 40:02.225
♪ I don't wanna be your hero

40:02.269 --> 40:05.011
This is your stop.

40:05.054 --> 40:08.536
I wish I didn't have to
go up there.

40:08.580 --> 40:10.146
I know you think I'm being
your shrink,

40:10.190 --> 40:12.366
but you two really
need to talk.

40:12.410 --> 40:16.326
We've been trying
for years.

40:16.370 --> 40:19.417
Is that why you offered
to drive us?

40:19.460 --> 40:22.463
You needed a friend.

40:22.507 --> 40:25.901
Is that what we are?

40:25.945 --> 40:28.643
Friends?

40:28.687 --> 40:32.430
The same thing that
attracts me to you,

40:32.473 --> 40:34.301
terrifies me.

40:37.913 --> 40:39.349
Thanks for the ride.

40:41.526 --> 40:43.179
[ Seatbelt clicks ]As always.

40:43.223 --> 40:46.008
♪♪

40:46.052 --> 40:49.055
[ Car door closes ]

40:49.098 --> 40:54.495
♪♪

40:54.539 --> 40:58.891
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh

40:58.934 --> 41:06.159
♪ Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh

41:06.202 --> 41:10.511
♪ So let me go

41:10.555 --> 41:16.648
♪ I don't wanna be your hero

41:16.691 --> 41:20.739
♪ I don't wanna be a big man

41:20.782 --> 41:25.308
♪ Just wanna fight like
everyone else ♪

41:25.352 --> 41:32.054
♪♪

41:32.098 --> 41:34.535
People are gonna be looking
at the house soon.

41:34.579 --> 41:37.103
The Realtor wants it
to look nice.

41:37.146 --> 41:40.498
We should make sure
it's neat.

41:40.541 --> 41:42.543
It's empty, Dad.

41:42.587 --> 41:46.068
There's nothing in here
but us.

41:46.112 --> 41:49.507
You left the dishes in the sink.
I should wash them.

41:49.550 --> 41:52.422
Turns out Damon had
a lot to say.

41:56.905 --> 42:01.519
Robert screwed things up,
Dad...

42:01.562 --> 42:03.433
for a lot of people.

42:05.479 --> 42:07.655
They can't forget it.

42:10.353 --> 42:12.181
That's why
he killed himself.

42:15.054 --> 42:17.273
It's why they all did.

42:21.887 --> 42:25.064
I know how hard
this must be to hear.

42:25.107 --> 42:26.805
What's hard is you.

42:26.848 --> 42:28.589
I'm done.

42:28.633 --> 42:31.113
Do what you want
with the house. I don't care.

42:31.157 --> 42:32.941
I'm leaving.

42:32.985 --> 42:35.074
I don't have any sons left.

42:38.077 --> 42:41.689
♪ Let me go

42:41.733 --> 42:46.607
♪ I don't wanna be your hero

42:57.879 --> 43:07.497
♪♪
